@startuml BobaLink_TabGroup_Batch_Send
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2

title BobaLink — Sequence Diagram: Tab Group Batch Send

actor "User" as User #F3E5F5
participant "Context Menu\nbackground.js" as Menu #E8F0FE
participant "Background SW\nbackground.js" as BG #E8F0FE
participant "Tab Groups API\nchrome.tabGroups" as TGAPI #E8F5E9
participant "Tabs API\nchrome.tabs" as TabsAPI #E8F5E9
participant "Content Scripts\ncontent.js" as CS #FFF8E1
participant "BobaAPIClient\napi/client.js" as API #FFF8E1
participant "qBitTorrent\nWebUI :8080" as qBit #E8EAF6

== User Initiates Batch ==
User -> Menu: Right-click on Tab Group
activate Menu #BBDEFB
Menu --> User: Show context menu
User -> Menu: Select "Send all torrents"
Menu -> BG: contextMenus.onClicked
deactivate Menu
activate BG #BBDEFB

== Query Tab Structure ==
BG -> TGAPI: tabGroups.query({title})
activate TGAPI #C8E6C9
TGAPI --> BG: group[] with groupId
deactivate TGAPI
BG -> TabsAPI: tabs.query({groupId})
activate TabsAPI #C8E6C9
TabsAPI --> BG: tabs[] with tabId, url
deactivate TabsAPI

== Inject & Collect Per Tab ==
loop For each tab
    BG -> CS: scripting.executeScript({tabId})
    activate CS #FFE0B2
    CS -> CS: Scan DOM + parse
    CS --> BG: [{torrents: [...]}]
    deactivate CS
end

== Send Batch ==
BG -> BG: Flatten & deduplicate
BG -> API: sendBatch(torrents)
activate API #FFE0B2
API -> qBit: POST /torrents/add (batch)
activate qBit #C5CAE9
qBit -> qBit: Process all in parallel
qBit --> API: 200 OK + results[]
deactivate qBit
API --> BG: {added, failed}
deactivate API

== Complete ==
BG -> BG: Store in send_history
BG --> User: Notification: "N added"
deactivate BG

@enduml